; Phase 1 Dashboard Demo Program
; This G-code demonstrates the Phase 1 Dashboard Parity widgets
; It shows modal group changes, tool changes, and various machine states

; Start with initialization
G90 G54 G17 G40 G49 G94 G98 ; Absolute, G54 WCS, XY plane, no compensation, feed rate mode
G21 ; Metric units (shows units in modal HUD)
F500 ; Set feed rate

; Display message
(MSG, Phase 1 Dashboard Demo - Starting)

; Home position
G0 X0 Y0 Z25

; Tool change to demonstrate tool info panel
T1 M6 ; Load tool 1
S1000 M3 ; Start spindle (shows in status tiles)

; Demonstrate modal group changes
G0 X10 Y10 ; Rapid positioning (G0 in modal HUD)
G1 Z5 F100 ; Linear interpolation (G1 in modal HUD)

; Change to incremental mode
G91 ; Incremental positioning (G91 in modal HUD)
G1 X5 Y5 F200

; Back to absolute
G90 ; Absolute positioning (G90 in modal HUD)

; Change plane
G18 ; XZ plane (G18 in modal HUD)
G0 X20 Z10

G17 ; Back to XY plane (G17 in modal HUD)

; Change coordinate system
G55 ; Use G55 WCS (G55 in modal HUD)
G0 X0 Y0

G54 ; Back to G54 WCS (G54 in modal HUD)

; Tool change to demonstrate tool info update
T2 M6 ; Change to tool 2
M1 ; Optional stop (test optional stop toggle)

; Cutter compensation demo
G41 D1 ; Left cutter compensation (G41 in modal HUD)
G1 X30 Y30 F300

G40 ; Cancel cutter compensation (G40 in modal HUD)

; Tool length compensation
G43 H1 ; Tool length compensation (G43 in modal HUD)
G0 Z50

G49 ; Cancel tool length compensation (G49 in modal HUD)

; Change to imperial units
G20 ; Imperial units (G20 in modal HUD)
G0 X1.0 Y1.0

G21 ; Back to metric (G21 in modal HUD)

; Spindle off
M5 ; Stop spindle

; Final position
G0 X0 Y0 Z25

; Program end
M30 ; End program

; Notes for testing:
; - Use Single Block mode to step through and see modal changes
; - Use Hold/Resume to test cycle control
; - Tool changes will update the tool info panel
; - Modal group HUD should update throughout execution
; - Status tiles should reflect machine state changes